Working with huge datasets in LINQ vb and C#
==============================================

LINQ makes chunking, appending, and writing files surprisingly elegant — no complex loops, no manual counters.
Today I generated 450,000 zero‑padded numbers, split them into 100k‑sized chunks, appended them to a master file, and also wrote each chunk to its own file.
All with clean, functional VB and C#.

🧪 C# Implementation
=================
IEnumerable<string> numberslist =
    Enumerable.Range(1, 450000).Select(x => x.ToString("000000"));
Int32 chunkSize = 100000;
List<List<string>> chunkedNumberList = numberslist
  .Select((value, index) => new { Value = value, Index = index })
  .GroupBy(x => x.Index / chunkSize)
  .Select(g => g.Select(x => x.Value).ToList())
  .ToList();

chunkedNumberList.ForEach(x =>
{
    string filePath = "d:\\output_csharp.txt";
    File.AppendAllLines(filePath, x);
});
Int32 fcnt = 1;
chunkedNumberList.ForEach(x =>
{
    string filePath = $"d:\\output_csharp_"+ fcnt.ToString("000") +".txt";
    File.WriteAllLines (filePath, x);
    fcnt ++;
});


🧪 VB.NET Implementation
===================
        Dim numberlist As IEnumerable(Of String) =
    Enumerable.Range(1, 450000).Select(Function(i) i.ToString("000000"))
        Dim chunkSize As Integer = 100000
        Dim chunkednumberList As List(Of List(Of String)) = numberlist _
       .Select(Function(value, index) New With {.Value = value, .Index = index}) _
       .GroupBy(Function(x) x.Index \ chunkSize) _
       .Select(Function(g) g.Select(Function(x) x.Value).ToList()) _
       .ToList()
        ' Write each chunk to a one file.  
        chunkednumberList.ForEach(Sub(chunk)
                                      Dim filePath As String = "D:\output_vb.txt"
                                      File.AppendAllLines(filePath, chunk)
                                  End Sub)
        'write each chunk to a separate file.
       Dim fcnt As Integer = 1
 chunkednumberList.ForEach(Sub(chunk)
                               Dim filePath As String = $"D:\output_vb_{fcnt.ToString("000")
}.txt"
                               fcnt += 1
                               File.AppendAllLines(filePath, chunk)
                           End Sub)

                                  End Sub)
✅ Advantages 
Clean and readable LINQ pipeline — chunking, grouping, and indexing are handled elegantly without manual loops.
Flexible output handling — easily supports both appending to a master file and writing separate chunk files.
⚠️ Disadvantages 
High memory usage — the entire dataset and all chunk lists are fully materialized in memory.
